When a JIRA ticket is re-assigned, for example, both the old assignee and the new assignee are notified of the change.  I've been assuming that this also applies to changes for "reporter", but I haven't actually tested that case.

However, for a notification based on, say, a user list custom field, users who are removed from the field are not notified of that change.  This leaves the removed user possibly thinking that they are "in the loop", when they've really been cut out of it without notice.  This happened to one of our users last week, which is what prompted this submission.

My suggestion is that, for any event that results in a notification being sent to the users or groups in a custom field, that the notification use the union of the previous and current values of the field, instead of just the current value.

